AGI - The president of the Emilia Romagna region, Stefano Bonaccini>, will run in the European elections as candidate of the Pd in the North East constituency. To announce the dem secretary, Elly Schlein>.&nbsp; "The elections of 8 and 9 June are a decisive challenge for the future of Europe. And we must deploy all the best energies we have. For this reason I asked Stefano Bonaccini to guide the list of Northeast: its ten-year experience as president of Emilia-Romagna and its role as president of the PD make it a very strong proposal for the battle we must lead and the Europe we want to build. Thank you for accepting it," reads in the note from Schlein.
&nbsp;
"Care e cari emiliano romagnoli, today I decided to turn directly to all of you, the secretary of my party Elly Schlein asked me to nominate myself in the North East constituency of which Emilia Romagna is part, in the next European elections, thanking it I decided to accept", Bonaccini said in the video in which he announces his descent into the field, "today nothing ends, today is a new beginning. We still have a lot of road to go together."
&nbsp;
"For me ten years were very important, leading this region, beautiful, tiring, but very important", is the budget drawn by Bonaccini, "for me believe me, it was a long reflection, when I was elected the first time in 2014, I was aware of the responsibility I charged myself on the shoulders, we were at the lowest point in the history of Emilia Romagna because as you remember, participated in that vote little less than 40% of voters. We were in a period in which confidence in politics was at the very least, in the middle of a recession that had disrupted Europe, Italy and of course Emilia Romagna. Especially two years earlier, here two earthquakes at a distance of 9 days, had produced 28 victims and hundreds of wounded, over 12 billion euros of damage. Today, thanks to the extraordinary work we have all done together, Emilia Romagna is the locomotive of Italy".
&nbsp;
"It's not a farewell message, nothing ends. A new chapter begins. I have accepted the challenge of European elections because I am convinced that the future is more and more Europe", continues the president of the Emilia-Romagna Region, "it is for Italy that without a strong Europe, united, would run and count less and less, like the other countries individually taken of our continent. For Emilia-Romagna Europe is already present is the dimension with which we compare each day, with which we compare our enterprises, our territories being one of the most open regions in the world. Just look at the extraordinary results of our export. Despite that flood, we only missed that, that last year caused 9 billion damage our companies exported something like 85 billion reaching the record never reached in the history of this region".

